From 223d242d944901ed2676f1998888d281877c0e5d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ferdinando Terada <Ferdinando.GodoyTerada@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Feb 2026 14:48:33 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Fix IPv6 preferred lifetime for aliased interfaces

Change set_preferred_lft() to set 'forever' instead of '0' for
interfaces with colon in their names (e.g., vlan10:8-20).

Previously, IPv6 addresses on aliased interfaces were automatically
marked as deprecated (preferred_lft 0sec), making them unusable for
outgoing connections. This forced users to add workarounds in post-up
scripts to manually set preferred_lft to forever.

With this change, all IPv6 addresses on aliased interfaces will now
remain undeprecated by default, matching the expected behavior for
static IPv6 address configuration.

Signed-off-by: Ferdinando Terada <Ferdinando.GodoyTerada@windriver.com>
Signed-off-by: Abhinav Ayyapasetti <abhinav.ayyapasetti@windriver.com>
---
 archcommon.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/archcommon.c b/archcommon.c
index c7cf486..c0f397f 100644
--- a/archcommon.c
+++ b/archcommon.c
@@ -257,7 +257,7 @@ void set_preferred_lft(interface_defn *ifd, char **pparam, int argc, char **argv
 		return;
 
 	if (iface_has(":")) {
-		char s[] = "0";
+		char s[] = "forever";
 
 		*pparam = realloc(*pparam, sizeof(s));
 		if (*pparam == NULL)
-- 
